7 An Act relating to alcoholic beverages; amending 37A
O.S. 2021, Section 5-120, which relates to books and
8 records of licensees; requiring licensee to provide
certain books and records within a certain timeframe;
9 and providing an effective date.
10
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 37A O.S. 2021, Section 5-120, is
14 amended to read as follows:
15 Section 5-120. All licensees under the Oklahoma Alcoholic
16 Beverage Control Act shall keep books and records with regard to
17 alcoholic beverages which shall contain such information and
18 itemization thereof as the ABLE Commission may prescribe by rule.
19 All books, records, inventories, invoices and other accounting
20 documents required by the Oklahoma Alcoholic Beverage Control Act
21 shall be kept for three (3) years and shall at all times be
22 available for inspection, upon request, by duly authorized
23 representatives of the ABLE Commission or the Oklahoma Tax
24 Commission within ten (10) business days after being requested.
ENGR. H. B. NO. 3530 Page 1

1 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
2 Passed the House of Representatives the 9th day of March, 2026.
